# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __ipow__, __ilshift__, __irshift__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# All eighteen values are false. KEY FINDING: decimal.Decimal defines __pow__
# and __rpow__ (waves 660/664) but NOT __ipow__: Decimal is immutable and
# d **= x rebinds via __pow__. Decimal also does not define __lshift__,
# __rshift__, __ilshift__, or __irshift__: bitwise shift has no meaning for
# arbitrary-precision decimal arithmetic. Consistent with waves 666/667:
# no in-place operators present in decimal.Decimal.__dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

